included.occupation: Graduate student at University of Michigan (MSI)

included.name: The Johns Hopkins University Applied Physics Laboratory

included.description: Core coursework in research methods in usability testing and human factors, additional coursework focused on ed tech and game design, and a focus on methods in statistical analysis. Worked part-time in the Sirius Lab at JHU/APL. Further coursework and lab experience with psychophysiological equipment and eye-tracking and pupil dilation studies.

Completed majors in Physics and Cognitive Science, graduating cum laude. Worked as a programmer in a physics lab and a cognitive neuroscience lab. Served as the first peer-elected president of the Dartmouth Physics Society, creating job and networking opportunities for physics majors. Took advantage of a number of teaching opportunities, teaching middle and high school physics at TOPS at MIT, working at the Rassias Center as an Italian Assistant Teacher, and plenty more. Studied Italian, which included 10 weeks living with a host family in Rome.
included.activities: Dartmouth Physics Society, Dartmouth Sexual Assault Awareness Program, Summer Enrichment at Dartmouth, Dartmouth Outing Club Trips, The Dartmouth Society for Engineers After-School Science Program

included.name: Dartmouth Physics Society
included.description: Helped develop the infrastructure for an undergraduate physics society on campus, with continued work in organizing and supervising group activities, managing the executive board, and acting as a liaison with the Physics faculty and other inter- and intramural societies. Oversaw an increase in the membership and scope of the society by providing new networking opportunities, jobs for members, and resources for physics students.
Synthesized code in IDL and VPython to manipulate and model research data related to the BARREL balloon campaign, investigating regular atmospheric precipitation of relativistic subatomic particles.
included.title: Research Assistant

included.description:
Ads Quality UX - Search Ads
Conduct and direct research improving the design and features of several ads formats on the Google search page. Identify key stakeholder needs, propose, plan, and conduct research, and analyze and present findings to product teams to determine product direction.
included.title: User Experience Researcher

included.companyName: Johns Hopkins University Applied Physics Laboratory
included.description: Oversaw research, recruitment, and lab maintenance and management at George Mason University as the main testing facility for the Sirius Project at APL, and acted as a liaison with the GMU administration and institutional review board.
included.title: Graduate Research Assistant

included.description: Investigated the perceptual effects of mental illnesses such as schizophrenia and autism. Involved collecting data from outside sources and collating machine learning algorithms in MATLAB for data analysis.
included.title: Research Assistant

included.description: Conduct research and synthesize findings on tight timelines, collaborate with fellow UX researchers and leads to meet project needs spanning several stages of product development, and work directly with multi-disciplinary product teams, such as marketing, industrial design, and project leadership, to make findings actionable.
included.title: UX Research Assistant

included.summary:
User experience specialist with a diverse academic background and professional experience in all stages of usability, UX, and psychological research, in both academic and industry settings.

Expertise in writing and conducting interviews, developing, distributing, and analyzing surveys and questionnaires, quantitative data management and analysis, and reporting results of user tests. 

Further experience in participant recruitment, managing large research initiatives, running usability tests, conducting lit reviews and task analyses, and using psychophysiological sensors and eye-tracking for testing purposes.
included.headline: User Experience Researcher at Google

included.description: Poster presentation at Association for Psychological Sciences 2014 annual convention.
included.title: A Technique to Determine Mental Workload by Pupil Dilation on Varying Backgrounds

included.companyName: Dartmouth Society of Engineers After-School Science Program
included.description: Worked with a team to develop science-oriented curricula for after-school classes at local elementary schools, and visited the schools once a week to teach and interact with the students.
